      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MEPUNGA SCARLETT (7) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 1.75 lengths at this track in a handy 23.90 beating Mac And Cheese. Wide box to overcome but goes well over this trip. Expected to be right there at the finish again. GAS LANTERN (2) had some strong recent form but was below best last time when eighth (22.75) in a Grade 5 FIN at Ballarat. Shuffled back off the squeeze box last time and never in it. Form here at the trip sound including five wins. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Key runner on best form. SHE'S PRIMED (4) stalked the pace from a low draw last start and fought on well to finish 2.5 lengths away in second (25.58) at Warrnambool in a Grade 4/5 over 450m. Well-placed to take this out. DEVIL'S SYMPATHY (5) placed last time out at big odds - worth considering.",
